X
p
X
p=3/4
 {\rm P}(X=n)=(1-p)^{n-1} p, \;\; n=1,2,3,\ldots. 
 {\rm E}(X) = \sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {n{\rm P}(X = n)}  = \sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {n(1 - p)^{n - 1} p}  = \frac{p}{{1 - p}}\sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {n(1 - p)^n } . 
 \sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {n(1 - p)^n } = \frac{{1 - p}}{p} {\rm E}(X). 
 {\rm E}(X) = p \cdot 1 + (1-p)(1+{\rm E}(X)), 
 {\rm E}(X)=\frac{1}{p}. 
 \sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {n(1 - p)^n } = \frac{{1 - p}}{p} {\rm E}(X) = \frac{{1 - p}}{p^2}. 
 \sum\limits_{n = 1}^\infty  {\frac{n}{{4^n }}}  = \frac{{1/4}}{{9/16}} = \frac{4}{9}. 
